messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /api/users

All HTTP methods acceptable (override):
- false

HEAD:
- false

POST:
- true

OPTIONS:
- false

TRACE:
- false

GET:
- true

PUT:
- false

DELETE:
- false

PATCH:
- false

Explanation:
- In server.js the users router is mounted with app.use('/api/users', userRoutes); so every route defined in routes/userRoutes.js is prefixed with /api/users.
- In routes/userRoutes.js the root route (router.route('/')) has two handlers chained: .post(registerUser) and .get(protect, admin, getUsers). That makes /api/users accept POST (registerUser) and GET (protect, admin, getUsers).
- There is no router.all or app.all to allow all methods, so "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false.
- There are no explicit handlers for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH on the /api/users path in the code provided, so those are marked false. (Per instructions, this judgment is made strictly from the source code â€” implicit framework behaviors are not assumed.)
- GET is true because getUsers is explicitly registered for GET on the '/' route in routes/userRoutes.js (which becomes /api/users). POST is true because registerUser is explicitly registered for POST on the same route.
